$ PowerShell: common parameter -errorVariable

Invoking a → Windows/PowerShell/language/cmdlet with the → Windows/PowerShell/language/cmdlet#cmdlet-common-parameter[common parameter]
`-errorVariable` causes an error message (if the cmdlet failes) to be stored in the specified → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable[variable].

As is also the case with the → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/error[automatic variable `$error`], the type of the indicated variable is
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Collections/ArrayList[`System.Collections.ArrayList`] whose elements store
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Management/Automation/ErrorRecord[`System.Management.Automation.ErrorRecord`] objects.

